Dear town council I am writing in connection with your idea of banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants.
I would like to point out a few issues that I have with the solution you have created.
I reckon that this amendment could have a bad impact on youger part of our society as well as on the other part of residences of our city.
Nowadays phones are very crucial in our lives, therefore banning the use of them can discourage people from using public transport, moreover shopping market can go into reccesion, because people would be more willing to buy things via the Internet, without supporting local bussinesses which can lead to their bankruptcy.
On the other hand, I support banning use of mobile phones in restaurants.
I find that capability to talk to each other without using mobile phones might increase integration of the people between them.
I wish that could be truth and that neighbours could have better relations with themselves.
Furthermore, mobile phones are unreplecable in case of emergency.
To conclude, I believe you will make a good decision and I hope that you are going to make more research prior passing this law.
Even though I cannot agree with your idea, I am sure that with a few improvements it can be considered as a good move of our authorities.
Yours faithfully
As human beings we like to live in groups or belonging a society in this reason matches excatly with the animals so I am for both ideas even though they are contradictory .
Let me to point out some ideas.
The first point is to highlight that all animals deserve to be free and in their habitats , however , it is well knonw that most of them , specially wild animals such as tigers, lions and other big felines are haunted by insane hunters to trade thier fur and organs , in other words, we have to keep endangered animals in safe places and one of this place are the zoos .
Another point to discuss is that all live organisms must live in its habitats in order to develop and survive properly , in contarst the constantly growing all the cities have not avoid destroying vast natural areas affecting these natural habitats In summary we must think about how to run our responsabilitites to our nature and find the correct decisions.
I love animals, and I would always want the best for them, sometimes I think animals are better than people, or at least nobler, because animals only kill for food or for defender themselves, their puppies or their territory while men are able to kill for pleasure.
In the same way I think wild animals must live freely, in nature, in their environment.
In my opinion zoos are not a good place for wild animals above all traditional and old zoos where animals stay imprisoned in a small cage, suffering big levels of ansiety and bad behaviour of visitors, modern parks are a very different posibility where animals dispose of big spaces only for them while visitors can see them from a enough distance to do not disturb their life, but I really think the best for animals is living in an absolute freedom in the place where they was born in their natural environment surrounded by other wild animals like they lived time ago.
Other very important think is to take care of them, and I agree that it is easier in a zoo with vets close to them, but this is also possible to do it in a bigger space, perhaps with a big effort but possible due to the existence of poachers that represent a real danger and from whom it is necessary to protect the animals.
In this days it is more and more habitual that young people choose to study in another country for a more or less long period of time during high school or university, this decission has advantages and disadvantages.
For many students there would be an economic problem, because the most of them try to study in a university close the house of their parents to save money having the possibility to come back home every weekend for food for the week, moreover a univerity placed in a small town must be cheaper than in a foreign country, in addition to this, it is always possible that not all students feel desire to live abroad.
On the other hand it could be very interesting for young students to live alone in other country far to their families, inmerse in a different culture having the possibility to learn a new language and meet other people and perhaps following a different method in their studies, and the most important for me, living by themselves.
In my opinion, I believe that if it is possible, it will be better the option of going to study in another country for a time before endind studies.
Nowadays there are many opportunities to study abroad and there are not barriers to stop this tendency and most universities especially American and Europeans offer scholarships or special discounts on undergrauates and graduates programms .
Regarding the question I have some advantages and disadvanatges to mention in this paragraph .
About the first point I consider advantages to learn a new language and culture, these new elements help you to adapt to the new context where you are in and make you capable to deal with your academic life .
Secondly , being abroad gives you a new perspective of life and you feel renovated in your thoughts and finally you can have more chances to improve personally, maybe you can have more possibilities to get a job and keep on studying a postgraduate course , maybe y.
For disadvantages, I can tell the difficulties to adapt to the new way of life and this is common and natural but many ttimes this can become hard to overcome for the students and another point is to live alone for long time , most exchange students live in small rooms and they have limitations to interact with other studnets.
In summary studying abroad has advantages and disadvantes and the most important is to balance those features and look for the best options to over come them .
