At present, society is more competetive, so it is difficult to play outside.
IT technology improves and Internet affects the life of children, so video games is inevitable.
Otherwise I accept that video games have the tendency of additive, so it is important to make rules regarding playing video games.
Orginally, playing is not unmoral.
It is useful because it makes change the pace and relaxed.
Picture this: A woman who is a billionaire, lives in the biggest house of the neighboorhoud and has everything she could think of.
However is this woman not able to walk, due to an accident that has happends years ago.
Next to the woman lives another Woman, who is quiet poor, lives in the smallest house in the neighboorhood and has just enough money to buy the necessary things.
But this woman is healthy and able to do everything.
Who is the most happy and is the most fortunate?
The answers to this question is easy: the poor woman who lives in the small house.
She may hasn't a lot of money but she is able to do everything.
Walking, running, going to the supermarket, swimming, surfing, dancing etc.
The rich woman who lives in the big house can't do all this.
She needs for everything help and is only able to sit all day.
So If we look at this situation we can make a conclusion.
We aren't happy when we're always depended on everybody and when we aren't able to do just simple such as walking or running.
We may have a lot money but we can't buy a good health with that.
We can only buy things to make our lives a little better or more luxe.
But do we need al that luxery if we can't enjoy it fully?
