With the change of time, schools will also change in the future.
Teachers are still instructors but act as instructors rather than holding knowledge.
Students are completely autonomous, self-taught in the way they feel is most appropriate.
Course materials will therefore be much more vivid.
Geography or Astronomy classes, the entire Milky Way will be visible around students thanks to virtual reality technology.
Because technology can be more effectively utilized in certain areas, the curriculum will make room for skills that require only knowledge of people and direct interaction.
Thus, practical experience will be emphasized in the courses.
schools will remain educational places.
