Hi Jack, Thank you for your message and let me wish you an happy birthday.
Now, let take a look at how a birthday is celebrated in France.
To be honest, it's very quite similar as your description.
Indeed, especially when we are childs, we used to have a cake made by our mother with candies.
But generally, we celebrate our birthday twice.
The first time with our friends from school.
All mothers drop off their child in our house and then we spend all day playing various indoor or outdoor games.
Each guest brings a gift, often a toy, and we have the opportunity to use it after eating the homemade cake.
The second time, we celebrate our birthday only with our family either at home or in a restaurant.
These two celebrations have a common point. Both of them include an "Happy Birthday" song.
Then, when we become adults, each one celebrate his birthday depending on its mood.
Some still want to organize party with their friends. Others prefer more simple celebration surrounded by their family.
As you see, our culture is near yours about this important life's event.
I'm looking forward to hearing from you Seb
These last years, we can find out a important debate about education.
While some think that it is better for students to be followed by the the same teacher throughout his schooling, others believe that students benefit more from having new teachers each year.
Let's see what are the student's advandages of both of these perspectives.
In one hand , we can consider that having the same teacher during several years can be benefit.
Indeed, keeping a good relationship student-teacher for several years promote confidence.
Obviously, more a student increase his trust more it is more likely to succeed.
However, having a good relationship with a professor can't be a certitude.
Indeed, like other human interactions, a student may not match with his professor.
If this situation appears, the student suffers more the class than he takes advantage of it.
Thereupon, failure might occur.
In the other hand, having different teacher can be an opportunity, for the student, to access to different points of views.
Generally, hearing from different persons allows us to build our own perspective with shades.
Let's go further away telling that promote the understanding between people coming from different cultures.
Finally, to my opinion, pupils can benefit from having the same teacher.
Indeed, trust and confidence are part of the success for the youngers.
But throughout the schooling it's necessary to access to many views points for building a critical thinking.
