Since the early 2000's, the Internet has broken all borders around the world.
One lives in the age of exchange.
Information, knowledge, skills appear as resources more and more important.
Nowadays, global companies search for the better candidates throughout the world thanks social medias and digital applications.
In this context, I 'm going to present, to my opinion, the advantages and the disavantages fo studying abroad for students.
Firstly, I think that studying abroad is an opportunity.
In the current labor market, soft skills are as important as traditional work abilities.
Travels promote the development of these soft skills.
When a student chooses to study abroad, he goes out his or her zone of comfort.
He or she has to adapt to a new environment and find out solutions by himself in many daily situations such as rent an apartment, find a job,...
Also, discovering a new culture, meeting natives allows him or her to be an open-minded person.
Of course, learning a new language takes an important place in this student's development.
The ability to adapt, to understand others perspectives, to go out of the box and to speak many languages are for sure great advantages.
The main global companies are looking for these soft skills when they receive applications.
However, this global context has implied many inequalities between students around the world.
In fact, only some students will be able to travel or to access to these new technologies that is to say more likely students from developed countries.
The others will stay out of current labor requirements and only low paid and desinteresting jobs will be offered to them.
A main danger appears: create a social fracture between peoples and continent.
Finally, to conclude, I believe that studying abroad offers great personal opportunities but produces, in the same time, in\u00E9qualities and social risks between students that is to say between cultures.
We have to be careful not create a two speeds society.
