Dear Town Council, I would like to support your suggestion about banning the use of smartphones on public transportation and in restaurants and shops.
Primarily because I think that we spend way too much time on social media or on our phone in general and if we would concentrate on having conversations again, for instance in a restaurant, our social life would benefit extremely.
But besides holding us from communication, our smartphone use can also be a huge safety threat in public.
On the on hand for our privacy, because with them anyone is able to take pictures or videos of strangers and put them on the internet or share them with his or her friends, even without that persons approval.
On the other hand is it dangerous for your physical health in various ways.
First of all it is neither good for your eyes nor for your brain, but such a prohibitation could not help with those concerns.
Although what it may help with are reducing the many accidents caused because someone is distracted by his or her phone.
For example those incidents where someone is not paying attention while walking over the street or stepping into a train and falls, would be prevented.
Personally I do not really see the necessarity for such a ban in shops, because it helps with neither of the other concerns, but that is just my point of view.
In general I am supportive of that idea and hope it will be introduced apperantly.
Sencerily, Nele
Due to your advise to use Write and Improve on the Internet, here is a report about my experience.
I'm going to describe what I liked and what I disliked after using this Internet site to practise and improve my English writing.
In fact , this site offers many advantages.
First of all, it is free.
It's a very important point for students owning few economical resources.
You have access to many diifferent topics according to your level.
Then, the site appears clear and it is frendly-manner.
Indeed, you watch easily the different options offered to understand quickly how to use the site to improve your English skills and to set your goals.
Finally, you don't have to be patient to get your essays results.
As soon as, you click on the "Check Button," your result appears and the site highlights the incorrect sentences of your text.
To be honest, I have noticed a very few disadvantages.
I have only one regret.
As I have just mentionned previously, the site emphasises automatically your incorrect sentences.
However, sometimes it may be difficult for a student, to find the correct construction of the sentence without using a translator site such as Google Translate.
But even if we copy its translation in our text, we can get a worse grade.
To my opinion, this situation might sound quite confusing for someone who learns a language and doesn't master its shades.
To conclude, as the list of the advantages is bigger than the sole disavantage observed, I highly recommand my classmate to try this site.
It helps me a lot.
Since I was an young adult, I like travelling and discovering new cultures.
My first trips take me to Spain, Greece, Portugal that is to say countries located to the South of Europe.
I was used to travel alone.
Low living standards of these countries allow me to enjoy long-term period stays.
In June 2016, I went to London with my girlfriend for holidays.
This travel was very important for many reasons.
Firstly, it was our first travel abroad together.
What an exciting moment to discover new places and share his feelings with someone !
It's completely different than to live this moment alone.
We saw many places and sites such as the English Museum, the Wimbledon Stadium, the City's towers, Buckingam Palace,...
Unfortunately, the English living standards are very high and our stay could have lasted only a few days.
Secondly , it was my first holidays in an Anglophone country.
I really appreciated the culture, the rythm and the way of thinking of the natives.
Indeed, London seems a city that never sleeps contrary to Madrid that wakes up only in the afternoon and at night.
To conclude, it was the best holiday I ever had.
It was a way for us to know better each other with my girlfriend.
Also, after this experience I decided to learn in-depth the English language and culture.
In fact, I'm planning another trip to London.
But this time, I want to be able to speak more fluenty with the natives for a better experience.
It is a very good questions.
