I usually do exercise.
If I do not do exercise, I fell tired and many part of my body will are sore.
So, in my case doing exercise is important.
It is imortant to cope with a new day, so I usually do yoga just after I have awakned.
I do exercise every day due to I have no car.
In fact I use the bicycle.
So, I take the bus or I go walking just when it is raining.
Fortunatelly where I live often is sunny and warm.
Apart those cases I like running, ciclying or swim.
So I prefer doing sports than exercises, but yoga would be included in a sort of exercises category.
I do not like definetely exercising at a gym because the quality of air is not good and you are close in a room.
So I prefer open space.
Furthermore there are some kind of activities which in a gym result boring.
For example if I run in a gym up a treadmill, I feel bored but, surprisingly if I run outdoor I feel happy.
In the end I usually do yoga and cycling, I often run or swim and sometimes I skii which is something that I love, or others diferent sports when it is possible.
But definetely I do not go at a gym to do exercises.
