I have a scientist background, so I like medecine as a science, but I never wanted to become a doctor in despite of the degree in medecine is one of the most valued degrees, and many students compete to get a place to course it.
But the most of new doctors want to work in cities, mainly in a big hospital with a lot of medical devices and protected into a team of workmates with whom can discusse and compare decissions, and at the same time getting a bigger income and living in a city.
Accurately this is a real problem for rural life and for people who live in the countryside because actually there are not enough doctors in many rural areas, patients can live separated for long distances and the doctor have to drive from a place to other to assist them, in addition to this they are completely alone without modern devices and having only their personal opinion against the disease.
In my opinion a good way to solve this situation could be increasing the amount of money that rural doctors earn and putting enough means at their disposition to make tests that allowe them determinate different diseases in their patients.
I am retired now, but I was a mathematics teacher for thirty nine years in a Secondary School, my daily routine inmy job was bassed in non very long explanations and a lot of exercises, the most of them compulsory for every student, but I liked to propose some of them as volunteer and complementary work.
I know that today some schools require to their students a certain amount of volunteer work, I believe that I can say I was a precursor of this way to work that is followed now by many schools.
The volunteer work for students had only advantages for me in my career, because I always though that the main way to learn maths is doing exercises as much as posible, in addition to this practising with specialized problems require more attention for the students who will improve their learning more quickly, and for the teacher it is a perfect way to determinate accuratelly the interest and the level of knowledge of students who participate in these volunteer exercises.
