Many years ago the rol of the music in learning changed completely, before that music was absolutely forgotten in curriculums and programs, being restricted to Schools of Music.
In the earlies 90, music was included like a subject for all students in Secondary Schools, and a controversial situation was produced, because this measure was received in a very different way in each centre, while in some of them the new was happily accepted, in others was hardly critised, depending on the importance that music was considered in theirs, so it was possible to find diverse options from some ones where the music was not only compulsory but it was recommended that students learnt to play some musical instrument to other ones where the music was treated like a minor option.
Today, this situation is completely regulated, and learning to play an instrument considered like a complementary activity.
There is a spanish saying that says " In the middle the virtue is," and in my opinion it is completely appropriated in this case, studying music may be very interesting and useful for students but in a fair measure, like a subject more, and afterward each student will have freedom for leaning or not any musical instrument.
Healthcare is one of the main and core necessities of a country to flourish and provide its citizens complete security.
But for over some time, it is being observed that the system is failing to provide that security to the Doctors and as an outcome of it is a major outflow of highly qualified doctors to the other countries.
We need to locate the main reasons behind the outflow of Doctors and simultaneously we need to resolve this problem.
Most of the Doctors move out of the country to find better working opportunities that can bring their knowledge into application and they are valued and respected for that.
It will be unfair to say that there are no opportunities in our country but they are very sparsely available.
Many people go to other countries to earn good money and the same happens with the Doctors as well.
They opt for going out to earn money and a lot of it.
If we compare the ratio of their earning in and out of the country then we will find that they eran huge money in outher countries.
Some doctors don't go to other countries in search of money but they find easearch work more attractive in those countries in comparison to home country.
This can be taken care of if the governmnet put money in research projects locally and build a good research environment.
This step will help the government in keeping the Doctors to domestic grounds but it will help in shaping the innovation field which would lead to the overall growth of the country.
