First of all, speaking about future we should specify what we mean by future, is this years or decades.
It seems to me that in short term there will not be dramatic changes as concerns schools.
A huge change has already been made in recent years thanks to the internet.
Students have much easier access to various information, they don't have to go to library to get them, there are many useful and reliable internet websides which are a lot of help.
I think that in future the use of internet in schools will be even more expanded.
Online lessons may be more common.
As concerns teaching content, it's probable that learners will be tought more practical knowlege than theory.
Instead of teaching children advanced mathematics formulas and schemes, they will be able to cook numerous dishes from different cuisines or sue pants by themselves.
Special emphasis should be put on classes where children are taught how to accept themselves , strenghten their self confidence and be stress resistant.
The only thing will remain the same - learning!
Nobody will do it for children.
