The zoos are not places to study animals.
The people goes it just for fun.
If you want to know about nature, you will search on internet or cinema or in another place.
In my point of view, the zoos responds a neccesity of entreteinment.
On the contrary, we can analize the figures of national parks and natural reserves, when the animals can live in they own terms.
This places are special desing for watching and studying nature and learn more about the animal behavor.
Yelowstone park is an important institution that illustrate my idea.
In the recent years, this park have contributed for the biological investigation.
For instance, the paper of "wolves and the relationship between predators and speces control" explore the impact of the wolves and explains how the predators deliver a hudge role inside the environmental.
On the contrary, the zoos doesn't expose the real condtions about the life of animals, it just shows an artifitial bioma.
In sumary, I think zoos aren't good places for learn about animals.
For my perspective, this kind of places should close, because it doesn't contribute for investigations.
Actually, the zoos is one of the most dangerous places for animals.
Dear Paul, I am just jotting down these few lines to remind you the tasks I would like you to perform while I am out of town for a get-away holiday.
First of all I would be grateful if you could water the plants in the pots inside the house, as well as water the rose garden outside, which is otherwise likely to wither under the scorching hot of the last days.
Next, there is the mail.
