We need to move on the new era.
Video Games can offer a new way to learn.
The parents have to incorporate it in her children routine rather than hide their childrens of the technology.
Video Games teache children how to resolve complex prbolems in an especific context.
Acording with a study of the Texas College, children are developing new skills with video games.
For instance, Minecraft explains how to build a person inside society, and another study of the National University of Colombia demostrated that fifty percent of their studients learnt english with video games.
It is false that video games can have a negative impact in children education.
Instead the benefits of the video games, parents have to create good habits with their children.
If they let alone their children with ganes then they would have educational problems.
Parents can't pretend that video games will educate their children.
The real problem is forget their role in the educational process.
They have to privided time and ourchase the habilities to understand the children's necessities in education.
You can't wipe out the tecnologies in the childrend growing process.
On the contrary, they have more work to do in the new era.
Don't struggle with the future, prepare yourself.
The school of the future will be different.
We may not be flying with rocketboots to school, but there will be big changes.
At first will there be newer and more modern subjects.
Those subjects will connect to all the new jobs that have appeared.
Subjects like 3D-printing and modern Technology such drones or Virtual reality may exist.
However do I think that we still keep our basic subjects such as Maths, English, history physics, which will change and develop with its time of course.
Our schools will be more digital in future.
I think more teachers will work from home and give their lessons via skype for example.
If we look really far in the future a teacher may give their lesson from home, which we can see via a hologram.
Our staff for the cafeteria and cleaning may be replaced with robots, so everything can become more cheap and quicker.
So enough to look forward to, with this modern School.
Everybody nowadays has an television.
