In my opinion is a television good for entertaining and eduction.
This is mainly because you can learn from a program that is made for entertaining and you can be entertained by programma that is made to educate us.
When we watch for example a gameshow where people need to answer difficult questions in order to win something, we are entertained.
However we are also educating ourselves with all the new facts we get know from all the questions answered to the participants.
If we look at this from the other side we'll come to the same conclusion.
For example when were watching a documentary we want to get to know more about a certain subject.
Although we will educate ourselves with all the new information told, we are still entertained too.
We think a suject is interesting and we want to know more about it, so we will like watching the documentary and we will be entertained.
A television is thus good for eductation and entertaining.
The problem of Television One of the most controversial technologies of the twenty century is Television.
At the beginning of the last century, people belived that the education could emerge from this little box.
In the first epoque of television the goverments have a different conception about culture and entreteinment, the culture was concived like a method to unite people for a particular goal.
Ideas like nation, moral or religion were implanted in the american houses.
But the Cold War brought another use for television and entreteinment.
Used to show the capitalist way of life, television was industrial produced and comercializided.
Every single house had it one.
Beverly the companies undestood television like a publicity car, they used television to create easy products to consume.
Television series, familiar movies or saturday morning cartoons used to be the perfect platforms to show their products.
Furthermore, they introduced the idea of consume in the ordinary life in whole American Country.
In the recent time, Television is use for both things: educating and entertains.
The central point is that television is using to educate people to hate culture and knowledge.
