Dear Leyla, How are things with you?
I bet you are still feeling knackered after your sleepless night.
I heard it through the grapevine that your party was a real blast and it went on till the small hours!
I wish I was there!
Take it from me, I feel terrible for not being able to put in an appearance yesterday night and to wish you happy birthday.
I hope you will forgive me once I have told you the reasons for my absence.
As you might recall, I have been toying with the idea of competing in a poetry prize for a long time.
It is a dream I have been nurturing since my childhood thanks to my grandmother, who used to spend her afternoons reading me the most famous poets\u2019 sonnets.
Well, to cut a long story short, I came across an advertisement about a poetry competition for teenagers in New Castle.
In less than no time I submitted my application with a poem titled "A sunset tinged with gold," and, guess what, I ended up winning the first prize!
The award ceremony was scheduled last night, and that is the reason why I could not come to your party.
Anyway, stop talking about me!
I cannot wait to know all the juicy gossip about your party!
How was it like?
What were you wearing?
Who were the guests?
What happened?
And how about your presents?
Come on, fill me in on every tiny detail.
Our mutual friend Jason told me he had a whale of a time at the party.
I happened to bump into him this morning and he could not help but heap praise on everything concerning your event.
Not only he extolled the virtues of the catering service, but he also sang the praises of the rock band you had hired in order to spice up the atmosphere.
He said that even the rain could not put a damper on your special night.
Finally, I would like to make up for my absence at your party inviting you at my house for a special weekend.
We could go for a stroll along the lakefront, or we could spend some quality time together sunbathing on the shore of Lake Como.
I am sure it will be a weekend of sheer relax, as well as of social whirlwind!
I am looking forward to seeing you.
Sarah
