Hi Rie, Thank you very much for your invitation!
I am thrilled to bits at the idea of coming over to your place tomorrow evening.
It has been ages since we last saw each other, and I am dying to catch up with all the news I have been missed while I was abroad for my job swap.
It goes without saying that I am glad to accept your invitation and I do relish the idea of spending some quality time together reminiscing about the good old times.
When it comes to my dietary requirements, I feel duty bound to give you a fair warning.
As you may recall, I have always been a bit of a fussy eater.
First of all, having a history of gastrointestinal disease, I have no alternative but to eat gluten-free bread and pasta.
Secondly, as I suffer from food allergies, artificial colours and preservatives are banned from my daily eating habits.
Thus, I will be forever deprived of the pleasure of tasting savoury snacks, bags of salty crisps and spicy hot ready-made meals, which are exactly the things that make people\u2019s mouth water.
In addition to that, I have recently become a non-meat eater.
I decided to give up eating meat in order to reduce my carbon footprint and do my part in tackling global problems, such as pollution and climate change.
Given this long list of dietary requirements, I cannot help but asking you to prepare a light but nourishing meal.
If I were you, I would serve a fresh and quick salad.
If I remember rightly, you are a master in preparing a salad with melon and tomatoes drizzled with mint dressing.
I really fancy something savoury and vibrant, too.
I am sure that this recipe will make the most of the summer\u2019s ingredients.
As a main course, I would go for a tray of dairy produce which is so refreshing in the dog days of summer.
I am well aware that it is not what you would call a slap-up meal, but it is a dinner that caters for girls, like the two of us, who have to count the calories!
What\u2019s more, we can keep a bit of a room for some pudding, which is a must for girls, like the two of us, who have a sweet tooth!
I am looking forward to seeing you tomorrow evening!
Have a good day Jessica
