It is a widespread belief that learning English is a gateway to a fulfilling and rewarding professional career.
I firmly believe that it is true.
Nowadays, a comprehensive knowledge of English is of paramount importance for those who aim to carve out a successful career abroad.
As far as I am concerned, mastering English well enough to work in an English-speaking country is one of my most cherished dreams.
There are plenty of reasons that prompted me to acquire an extensive knowledge in this language.
First of all, I would like to draw attention to the beneficial effects that an excellent grasp of English is sure to have on my career path.
As a professional journalist, I have been nurturing the lifelong ambition of working at The Washington Post since I was a child.
Now that I am a grown-up woman, I am determined to make this dream come true.
Honing my English skills is likely to boost my chances of getting a foot in the door at this world-renown newsroom whose journalistic tradition is a pillar of democracy.
Next, it is my firm conviction that an advanced level of English is an immense asset when it comes to building relationships.
As a lingua franca, English is understood everywhere, thus making it easier for people to communicate.
By socialising with people all over the world, I am supposed to strike up new friendships, rub shoulders with the movers and shakers in the media industry, as well as get in contact with new cultures and broaden my horizons.
Finally, there is no denying that the journey of learning English has brought out the best in me, revealing a burning desire to see the world and a remarkable gift for languages which I am certain will come in useful in the long run.
