If zoos are good places to learn about animals or a bad place because animals are not free is a good question and it is difficult explain what is the correct choise because there are many factors to consider.
First of all we have to think about envinroment which is not ideal for wild animals.
Furthermore it is very difficult to simulate the original diet of the animals which they can find in a forest or wood.
Anyway, I am sure that usually in zoos the staff is formed and competent.
I can imagine some biologists who can create the best condition nevertheless zoos represent an artificial habitat for the animals.
In my opinion it is hard to be pro or against zoos.
When i was child I remember I went to visit a big zoo with my family.
It was enormous and you could enter just with car.
So animals were free because there was no fence.
Of course there was a limit but animals lived all together and in an enormous space.
I remember a very fancy scene.
In fact a curious ostrich put his head inside the car because the window was a little bit lowered.
Everybody inside the car shouted but not in negative sense because that bird was scaring but funny at the same time.
So I decline a precise answer due to it is relatively complex for me to explain wath is the best option, but I am convenced that zoos might be as the zoo where I went to my family when I was child.
