In my opinion, health and richness work together.
In order to understand my perpective, I think it is important to have a closer look at the words health and rich.
Firstly, we usually associate health to our physical state and how well is our body.
But, today, in particular in a lockdown period, we notice that mental health is also very important.
Many people suffer to not be allowed to work and earn money.
They feel bad to see their desires, their wishes, theirs ambitions not accomplished.
Aslo, their social status is very important.
Feeling useless with an incapacity to climb the social ladder, they find themself in a moving situation.
Earning money is crucial for a balanced life.
Secondly, we can't sum up rich as how much money we have in our account.
The ability to learn, to acquire new skills, to have friends and to understand other points of view can be consider to be rich.
This process has a main role in the balanced life we are looking for.
To conclude, to be rich is essential to maintain a good health.
Lifestyle has always been a debatable issue due to its significant impacts on many other aspects of life.
Many believe that a peaceful life is a way to enjoy life, while the other regards a life with more intensity is a better life even when they have to spend a shorter time living.
From my perspective, I believe that being able to live for a century with calmness and being relaxed is the greatest way to live.
On the one hand, living an intensive life will disable one from knowing the greatest meanings of life.
However, a life full of intensity includes many dangerous or even illegal activities such as participating in racing events, doing drugs and living an unhealthy life.
A report from the University of Michigan demonstrates that those who enjoy racing, drugs share a similarity of living shorter than those who do not.
On the other hand, a calm life creates individuals numerous opportunities in their life.
People are unable to avoid mistakes in their life.
For some people, they always find themselves in trouble almost every day.
Some mistakes will lead to no consequences while some will have a significant impact on an individual's life such as their family, career, and happiness.
Therefore, if one chooses a calm life, he will create the ability to redeem his mistakes.
A psychology laboratory in Netherland shows that most successful people live a longer life because they put effort into trying a better solution to the problem but not becoming pessimistic and feeling regretful about what they did.
In conclusion, a long life does not only provide us chances to witness the greatest parts in life but also let one fixes what he has done wrong.
Hello Tom, I'm wrting you in connection with the concert I went last week.
I decided to go to this concert because it featured the world famous popstar Shakira for her first concert in England.
I'm a big fan of her.
Also, many other british groups should have performed in order to earn some donations to help people hitten by a tsunami in Asia.
But you certainly won't believe me.
All of a sudden, one hour after the beginning, the regional energy supply was destroyed by a storm.
There was no electricity in Liverpool where the concert was taking place.
Finally, I had to be back earlier than planned without seeing Shakira.
What a pity !
The purpose of this report is to evaluate "Write and Improve," an internet device to enhance the written English skills.
Among the plethora of English tools to improve your language skills, "Write and Improve" is offering comparatively many advantages and only a few flaws.
First, this English device is to use for free, secondly, it corrects the written input immediately and thirdly, it allows you to choose among 3 levels, among beginner level, intermediate and advanced.
A majore disadvantage is that the tool is reduced to check your written skills.
Language is not only based on producing written texts.
Other basic and fundamental competences, such as understanding, interaction and rules in linguistics are neglected almost completely.
Nevertheless, personally I would reccommend this fine tool to everyone who wants to determine the own speed of development of his written skills in English.
