Telling the truth is very important, I think so.
But in our lives, we have learned many lessons for the result of telling the truth.
We must know when we need to say the truth and when we must avoid that.
I have experienced with my ex-girl friend that story I still remembered util now.
By the time, I was a student, I falled in love with her and she had a best friend.
She asked me to teach them about math, physical and biology.
I couldn't find any reasons to say no.
I am a good person, I still have no ideas on seraparate what story must tell and what the story never tell the truth.
That night, When I texted messages to her, her's friend texted me too.
I must reply both of them.
But I forgot that who is the prior person.
I still texted one by one until she get the delay response from me.
She was so angry and asked me why.
I told her the truth that I was texting to her's friend.
After that, she wasn't reply to me again and she thought I have some problems with her's friend.
I tried to explain to her and gave many reasons to find the answer.
Even though, I came to her but her tried to avoid me.
This is a short story that I still remember.
So I believe that telling the truth at when and where is the most important things than just telling the truth.
