Dear Sir/Madam, I am writing to you to express my extreamely gratitude about your initiative.
I believe that banning the use of moblie phones on public transports and in shops and restaurants is the best decision you could make, beenig an absolutely necessary measure for the citizens health and wellness.
I consider this, because it is wellknown how the radiation of the phones affects humains' health and that it is amplified in the means of transport.
Judging by how many people are every day at every hour on the public transports, we can equal the radiations level they are exposed to, to a situation in which the people are all gathered in a microwave.
Also, the using of mobile phones should be banned from the resaurants and shops too.
Most of people go shoping, esspecially in malls, not just to literally do their shopping, but to relax.
The problem is that all of them have phones and are using them for surfing the Net, looking on Instagram, Facebook and anything alse.
This results again in actually heating the people in radiation.
So the banning of the mobile phones, at least in the big markets, like malls, is a well-founded decision.
As well, restricting the phones in restaurants is an exellent move to improve the citizens health.
It would be better if the peole could have dinner or lunch out and see the restaurant as a place of relaxing and socializing, not a place where all people have their eyes stucked on the screens and do not have the slightest ideea of what is happening around them.
I look forward to hearing from you asa soon as possible, Yours faithfully, Anne Austen
