It is well-known that a healthy lifestyle is provided by sport activites done with frequency so, as far as I am concerned, the proposition that all university students and school children should be forced to practice sport activities at least 3 times per week is a good intentioned one and I one agree with.
First thing first, inactive lifestyle is a problem all the humanity is confronting with nowadays.
Because of the developement of technology and the constantly increasing level of living standards, people are often choosing sedentarism to the detriment of sport or phisical activities.
People are moving from home to work or school and backwards by car or by means of transport instead of walking, either because of confortness or facillity, for that many cities are too wide to be able to move around walking.
This is the reason why they spend almost their entire day sitting; they sit at school or at work, sit in the car or public transports, sit at home watching a movie at TV or browsing on the phone.
Therefore, it will be a major succes if at least the children and students will practice some sports 3 times a week.
Also, schoolers and students are the most prone categories for inactivity, because studying ocupies most of their time as so they spend more than half a day sitting on a chair.
Although they can spend their breaks and their free time to relax outside and practice some phisical activities like jogging or playing sports with friends, the opption they choose is not always the healthy one, most of them prefering to spend the free time chatting and surfing the Net, or simply watch some movies.
If not the sport at school, this inactive lifestyle would lead to severe spine deformations, bone fragility and many other deseases.
Finally, I consider that the decision of making soprt in schools and universities mandatory is the right one, keeping in mind the inactive lifestyle everyon adopts today, in spite of an active one.
