Healthy lifestyle can contribute to better results at school.
Numerous studies have concluded that etc.
Encouraged to Explain the benefits Everyone should have the ability to choose for themselves Many people believe that it is imperative for schools and universities to make sports activities mandatory due to the life-threatening consequences of an unhealthy lifestyle.
However, I have to disagree with this statement, as I believe personal health should be exclusively in the hands of the beholder.
First, students and pupils ought to be in charge of their own lifestyles.
Should the educational institutions impose regular sports activities, the children may not agree with them.
What is more, even a sense of hatred towards these healthy practices could be developed by students.
For example, imposing sports in schools or universities could label them as useless, and even be ignored by most children.
Thus, forcibly applying such activities can have a negative impact on students.
Second, explaining the benefits of a healthy and active lifestyle are proven to be more effective than obligating students to do such activities.
Studies show that people tend to continue healthy practices given that they understand the benefits of them.
As a way to illustrate this, including educational activities on how to include sports in students' daily life rather than forcibly integrating them in schools is more likely to ensure that they will continue living healthily, provided that they understand the usefullness of an active lifestyle.
On the other hand, including sports activities in school can improve students' results.
Research concluded that working out regularly, which can be achieved by including such activities in schools, can boost the results and the overall results of students.
However, I do not find it appropriate to force children to undergo these kinds of activities.
In conclusion, imposing sports activities for students is certainly not the most suitable way of leading them into healthy lifestyles.
In spite of that, regular exercise could also be beneficial for the results of the students.
