Nowadays, our biggest wish as humans is to live as many years as possible.
The development of technology facilitates the medical treatments for curing people, assuring they are healthy, increasing the chance of living a longer life.
But is it all about how many years we wander around in this world?
To begin with, at the end of our lives, we don't concentrate on how many years we have lived.
Many cultural figures, such as Abraham Lincoln, have exemplified this concept.
One of his most famous quotes is "in the end it's not the years in your life that count; it's the life in your years\u201D.
We look back with nostalgia at our favourite moments we went through, cherishing the astonishing emotions and feelings we experienced.
Not only do they increase the intensity of a moment, but also create more powerful memories than the ones of somebody who might choose to live a calmer life.
To a further extent, embedding people with cherished memories increases the intensity of those moments, thus we become more attached to our beloved humans.
Living a longer life comes at the cost of seeing our close friends and relatives die.
This certain cycle of life might bring sorrow in somebody's life.
But this sorrow could be overcome if there are a lot of cherished memories from living life to the fullest, together with our buddies.
Taking everything into consideration, I consider that it's better to live a shorter life that is more intense.
That's how I want to spend the years of my life!
Nowadays, sedentarism affects most students who decide to adopt an inactive lifestyle.
It has a negative impact on our health, thus increasing the chances of contracting mortal diseases.
Moreover, technology provides to ourselves a cozy alternative to spend our time.
We don't realize how fast we damage our sight.
But is it that difficult to connect with nature?
I consider every student should be forced to do as many sportive activities as possible.
Firstly, an active lifestyle increases our immunity against multiple viruses.
The contact with nature exposes us to multiple variants of bacteria that stimulate our immune system to fight against them, albeit not being harmful to the human body.
Not only does an active lifestyle protect us from getting ill, but it also increases the quality of our sleep.
Scientists proved that people who spend their time doing outdoor activities are feeling revitalized when they are waking up, no matter how turbulent their sleep was.
Secondly, our health is affected spiritually.
We forget how to socialize with each other.
We spend too much time scrolling down on social media apps, counting on an app to transmit a specific message.
Practicing a team sport helps in increasing awareness of the others' feelings, thus developing communication skills.
If I would have known that I can understand better my friends after taking part in these activities, I would have joined my local football team years ago.
Concluding, doing sports activities in a school is beneficial for the students.
I don't consider that, with 3 times per week, this represents an exhausting activity that overwhelms the children.
