To, The Town Council, Murray Road, Nevada.
Respected Sir, This is to inform you about the opinion of the Council of Men on the proposal of mobile ban in public places.
The Council of Men sincerely disagree with this idea for a number of reasons.
Mobile phones have become an essential part of our daily lives.
People rely on their digital assistant for the completion of their chores.
Some of them have old parents, whom they keep in touch with via their mobile phones.
They monitor their activity via their phones.
Others have office work, children and their entire social life in their mobile phones.
Thus, banning mobile phones will be unacceptable by the public and may lead to an outrage.
To avoid such a situation, we propose a solution of limiting the usage.
We can pass a bill to limit the time spent on the mobile phones to thirty minutes in a public place.
The pubic will then use their mobile phones only for important tasks and not for idling away their time.
This will enable them to focus on their surroundings and people instead of hiding behind their screens.
This solution not only builds upon the intention behind the original bill, but also takes care of the health and security of the people.
With people priortizing their tasks on their mobiles, we can expect to see a more lively crowd in the restaurants.
I request you to kindly go through our proposal and make your decision.
Thanking you, Yours sincerely, David Hutton, Head of the Council of Men.
The role of music in learning process Music is such an important tool in human history.
Every society on Earth have been in contact with it for different uses.
Althoug, our develop like societies has a strong relation with music.
Besides, music is not just an entreteiment process or a hobby.
With that idea on mind it is easy to conclude that Schools need to integrate it in the learning process.
But the importance to study music doesn't limit to a cultural reference.
In the recent years, many universities studyed the way that music can improve the capacities of the brain in a numerous neural process.
For example, a Harvard paper concluded that the students who play music have better learning qualities than students who don't.
Thus, the University affirms that diversification is a necessary condition in the modern studies plan.
Other important point about learning music is the psycological.
Many authors had stablished that our musical preferences shows and defines an important part of our personality.
Due to music is the best mechanism to show it.
According with the german writer Federich Nietzsche, life without music is a mistake.
Music plays and important role inside the learning process.
It force doesn't imply just entretaiment.
There must be an art department in every school.
Students should have chance to choose painting or music.
All students should take art lessons but it may differ according to their abilities.
Some students might be talented in music and other students might be talented in painting.
What is certain is that art is benefical for all students.
They have to study art.
Art improves their personalites.
Some of them might not be very talented in music but they want to learn music.
In this case they cannot go to a music school but they should be educated in normal schools.
All students should be educated.
Music is useful for all people.
The ones should go to music school who want to be professional in music. For example I love music however I am not very talented in music.
Fortunately I study music at my school and I can play the guitar.
I love playing the guitar.
It makes me feel joyful and happy but I am not good at it.
I play it as a hobby.
I do not want to play it as a job so I should not go to music school.
The purpose excuses the means.
As Machiavelli said, I agree and am on the same page.
