Answering the following question: Exercise is important for our health, but are there things that are more important?
I think that yes, there are things that are more important because when we said exercise is important for our health we are focusing in body, but there are also mental health, whick I think is the most important question byt the reason that our body is a complex structure formed by material and immaterial elements: physical body and mental body.
And neither of these elements exists without the other.
So my assessment of whih part is more important is personal and I think the emotional is more important, the mental health for me in this moment is the most important think because that also sustains me and I don't see schools propagate this idea.
Post-pandemic mental health has gained importance and at that moment I realized how important this part is in my life.
