But as I said that sorry for I can't attend.
Please accept my apologise.
Maybe we can meet next week.
I will order a coffee for you to make it up my mistake.
We will talk about your party and we can gossip about what happened at your party.
I wish enjoy about your party, enjoy it.
But please dont drink too much. Because I want to listen everything about your party from you.
Take care Alex.
Best regards.
Well, I have a few favorites indoor activities.
What one I choose to do is mostly up to what I feel like doing that day or moment.
I really enjoy cooking.
I'm capable of cooking since I was a kid, and I'm used to cooking for me and my parents every day.
This is an activity that relax me a lot.
I've always been capable of forgetting all my daily problems while I'm cooking something tasty.
The last time I cook was yesterday, and I'll start to cook when I'll finish to write this.
Besides, I like to play video games.
I've played video games since I was a kid too, and I really enjoy doing it.
I rather rol and strategic games than sports games, and I think I've played almost every game that I've wanted.
However, I look forward to buying the newest Final Fantasy game soon, but it's very expensive now.
I don't want to expend too much in a simple video game.
Last but not least, I enjoy to do exercise, like bycicle or push-ups, in home.
I fell really healthy doing that, and this activity help me to get rid of the daily stress.
Hey Alex, I hope you are doing well.
I have some bad news for you.
I need to go abroad to handle an urgent business problem about the office I work at.
As a matter of fact I won't be able to participate at the party you invited me to.
I sincerely apologize for not attending to your party.
As I said due to the problem i'm having with my boss, i have to go to Italy tomorrow morning.
I guess tomorrow at this time I will have ate my Italian Pasta.
Therefore ofcourse I didn't forget, I will buy you Italian magnets as you wanted from me before.
I don't want to forgot to mention that I'm looking forward to meet you next Sunday. So that we could have brunch before we go to shopping for Christmas.
Write me soon so that I will try to arrange my work.
See you!
Well, I use my computer all the time now.
I started to use it when I was fifteen to play games and use social media, but, when I started college I needed to begin to use to study, to do my homework and essays.
When I finished my career and started my doctoral thesis, I started to live glued to my computer to do my thesis.
Now I use my computer for many things, although meanly for work, in order to write my articles and studies.
I can't wonder how I would do every thing I do without a computer.
It's a very useful thing, and makes my live and work a piece of cake.
Well, I enjoy my work, but I enjoy more use my computer to watch TV series and movies; to read books and the news, and to take a look to the social medias.
How I said before, I literally live glued to my computer.
Just now I'm using it to study English, to write this essay for this writing practice.
Without it, I can't manage to learn English so fast how I'm doing it.
Hi there, Matt, I know.
I'm a little upset about the end of the holidays.
I usually got melancholy in this final days.
I have to say good bye to my family and friends and get back to home for the school.
It's a pretty awful experience.
Well, we can't do anything about it.
Yes?
Will you have to improve in maths and history?
How bad were your degrees in that subjects last year?
Yes, I need to improve my English because I want to make an intership in London next year.
I need to learn a lot.
I'm going to join to the English club at school and enroll in a lenguage academy.
Besides, I was thinking to do other things by miself, like start to watch all the TV series and movies in English and use English applications like Duolingo or Write&Improve daily.
However, I really need to lose my fear to speak English in front other people.
I know a lot, I can understand practically everything what the people say in English, but I don't fell sure enough to try to speak with other people in English.
Maybe you could help me with this.
Hi there, Guess what?
I just finished to watch that movie I told you about it.
It was such a wonderful movie!
I wish you came with me to the cinema to see it.
You must enjoyed it a lot.
It was a movie called "Scream," and it was about a group of teenagers, a group of friends, which had to confront a misterious murderer who wanted to kill them all.
The mainly character was a girl, Sidney, who had a boyfriend, Billy.
The police suspected that he was the killer, since he was seen in a murder scenario.
However, while he was in jail, the murders continue, so they released him.
But, in the end, it was discobered that Billy was one of the murderer, and he had a accomplice, one of his friends, who help him to kill their friends, as a revenge of Sidney's mother, who had had an affair with Billy's father years ago, for which Billy's parents split up.
It was a crazy plot, but you spend all the movie imagine who is the murderer and why.
Would you like come with me to watch the movie?
I really want to watch it again.
Hi there!
I'm glad your birthday was so fantastic.
Well, it's the same, more or less.
I think the sort of celebration is mostly up to the person, and not in the country (or not in this case).
My birthdays were pretty same than your last birthday.
However, I know many people that celebrates his birthdays in a different way.
For my uncle's last birthday we all went to the beach, in order to have a beach day instead a traditional celebration.
For my sister's last birthday, she rent a bar to celebrate a big party, big a lot of buff, friends and even a DJ.
And for my grandmother last birthday, all my relatives, my grandmother and I went to a cabin at the mountains, to spend a whole weekend together.
My grandmother was very happy to see all us together and with her.
Therefore, I think that in my country we celebrate birthdays in the same way than in your country.
However, I know that in other countries birtdays are pretty different.
I watched a long time ago a documentary about this, and it was interesting to see how people celebrate and conceive this date.
Dear Leyla, I write you to apologise for not going to your birthday party yesterday.
I really wanted to go, but I had to deal with a serious problem: my mom got sick, and I had to brought her to the hospital.
They made a lot of tests, and it finally result that she had high blood pressure.
She is fine now due to the new medicament that the doctor prescribe her.
However, I had to spend all the evening and part of the night in the hospital.
That's why I couldn't go to your party.
How was they party?
It was fun?
Did you do something special?
What the guess gifted to you?
With regard to this, I was wondering if you want to do something with me next weekend, because I bought a special gift for you, and I want to give it to you.
Besides, I need to compensate you for not going to your party.
Maybe I can invited you to eat or dinner in a great chinese restaurant that is close to my house.
They do the best lemon chicken that I've eaten, and their rice three delicacies is wonderful too.
Well, I'm waiting for your answer.
See you soon.
Hi there, Rie, How wonderful idea!
Of course I'll be there!
However, maybe I'll arrive a bit late, since I have to work until half past six.
Last month my boss changed my working hours. Now I get off work later, and I start to work later though.
So I can't be there at 7 o'clock, but I'll be there only a few minutes later.
Shall I bring something to drink?
Well, I don't need nothing special.
I'll be happy to spend the night with you.
However, and only if you didn't mind, I would be glad to eat again that fantastic roast chicken that you made me years ago.
Do you remember?
I ate so much chicken that I had to lie down on your bed.
For desert, I think I will bring something.
There are a great bakery near my job where they make a wonderful chocolate cake.
Do you like chocolate?
If you didn't like it, I would buy a diferent cake.
Which type of cake are your favorite?
Well, I see you tomorrow.
Hi there, Luis: I'm very gratefull that you're going to look after my house while I'm on holiday.
It's a very kind gesture, and I pretended to return you the favor when you want it.
Would you like that I bring to you some gift?
Well, you asked me to tell you what you must do while I'm out.
It's only a few things, don't worry.
First, you must to water my plants.
I have a few in the kitchen, in the balcony and in the terrace.
However, you must not water my cactus, since they don't need much water.
Besides, you should feed my pets.
I only have a hamster and a pair of colour fish.
Since I'm going to be out only a few days, you don't have to clean the fishbowl or the cage. You only have to give them their feed.
Apart of this, I don't need anymore.
If you could collect my mail it would be perfect, but this is not necessary.
And, of course, if my house starts to burn, call the fire brigade.
I'm kidding, but if this happened, please, call them.
Thank you very much for everything.
See you when I'll return home.
Hi there, Ana, Yes, she has already told me that she had seen you while she was shopping.
Did you she her new haircut?
I didn't stop tell her to get a new haircut and she finally listened to me.
She seemed very older with her old haircut, and someone had to tell her the truth about it.
Well, I want to learn English for several reasons.
First, I think that knowing other languagues can offer you many job's oppotunities.
Besides, you'll be capable to travel around without any problem knowing English.
And, of course, you can enjoy movies, TV Series and books in English.
I already know enough to understand what the characters say in some TV Series, and I think it's quite better that listened the translated version.
However, there are other reason.
I've discovered that I really enjoy learning English.
When I was a child, I hated how they teached us English at the school.
I was actually a bad students, and I always got bad degrees in this subject.
However, I've found some ways to study English that I really enjoy, and I don't need to take a book and only study grammatical leason.
I don't want to write about my home town, so I'm gonna tell you about a city where I've gone in vacation: Gijon.
Gijon is a coast city in the north of Spain.
It's a fantastic touristic city with many things to do, specially in summer.
There are two main and big beaches with incredible waves all year.
Besides, in this city you can find many teathers, museums and even one of the biggest aquarium of Europe.
Unless you go there for at least four or five days, it's impossible that you see everything.
Due to is a touristic city, in Gijon you can find many hotels and motels to stay, depending on your economical possibilities.
For this very reason, there are many and wonderful restaurants.
In this restaurants you can find the typical food of this region, but there are restaurant of many types.
I'm thinking in a great italian restaurant where I ate the last time I was there. Their pasta and pizzas were marvelous.
During the night, you can find some fun in one of the several pubs and bars that you can find in this city, specially near the beach.
Hello there, Cristina, Carlos just told me about your car accident last week.
I didn't emailed you before because I hadn't heard anything until now, and I feel very sorry about it.
He said that you hurt your leg and one arm in the accident, and that you musn't leave home for two weeks in order to recover from your injuries.
Is thar true?
I asked him about the accident, but he didn't know much else.
How did it happend?
Were you alone when it happend?
Did someone else get hurt?
I really hope nothing more happend and you'll be totally fine as soon as possible.
Until then, I'll be there for you.
If you need something, you can call me, and I'll be there in a minute.
You were very helpful to me when I broke my leg two years ago, and I plan to return the favor.
Besides, I be used to helping people owing to my job at the Social Center.
So, What do you need?
By the way, I really want to see you.
When could I come over?
Cristina must want to come too, since she is your best friend.
I'll call her now to tell her about your accident, because she mustn't know anything yet.
I wish you'll be fine very soon.
Well, since I was and I'm a video game user, I don't have such a terrible impression about video games, but I recognized their dangers, though.
Many people think that you could have many problems, even mental issues, if you play video games.
However, in my personal experience, and acording to many researchs, playing video games with moderation can help you a lot with stress problems and other behaviors issues.
I've have always found a way to rest and forget my daily problems playing video games.
It's a very fun activity that requires your total attention, so you can turn off your mind for a while.
Besides, playing video games can help you to develop many mental and even physical skills.
You can improve your reflexes even.
It's true that some children can have serious problems with video games, since this activity easily can ditract them from their studies and other responsabilities.
However, this isn't really a problem caused for the video games, but for some incredibles lazy and careless parents who alow their children to spend to most of their time with their video games or phones.
Parents must put limits to this activities, and be responsible for their children, and not try to find excuses for their incompetence.
Well, I'm not sure about it.
It's true that animals must be in the nature and free.
However, the people need to know more about it.
How could you teach to a kid why is important to take care of the nature if you don't show him the animals that he must to protect?
It's important for all of us to know more to the animal world, to be close to the animals, in order to learn about them and love them more.
Besides, the kids love these places, and their trips at the zoo is a wonderful way for them to learn and have some fun.
I think that the real issue is how the animals are cared for in zoos.
If they're good, with enough food and clean water, and with enough space to run and make their lives, I don't see the problem.
However, it's true that in many places of the world, zoos aren't perfect places to the animals.
Furthermore, in many zoos are so many animals that it's impossible for their owners to take care of them.
So, I think that we must insist in better coditions for the animals who are in the zoos.
I do many thing during my free time.
However, I don't do the same things every day.
I like play video games since I was a child.
I'm used to playing video games at least ten or fifteen minuts daily.
I think this is a wonderful way to relax myself: If I have had a hard and stressful day, I can always find relaxation and peace killing some aliens or driving fast a car in a video game.
On the other hand, I really like to do exercise.
I didn't use to do exercise, but a few months ago I started to do it and it was wonderful.
I feel really well, and I've lost some weight even!
Besides, I really like to go out for a walk with my dogs.
I have two dogs right now, and they're marvelous.
One is pretty old, but the other one is young, and he always want to play with me.
The two of them are very affectionate, and they're always behind me, looking for a caress from me.
However, if they see me preparing the tub for their monthly bath, I can't find them anywhere.
Well, I think that my best holiday was during the last summer.
This wasn't only for the destination, but for how I was then.
Last year was horrible for me.
I had a lot of stress at work, but also something worse happended: my mother had a strock.
I was there when that happened, and it was terrible.
I was really terrified.
My mother survived, but she has to do rehabilitation for many months.
At the beggining she was very weak and dizzy, and I was alone to look after her.
She wasn't improve at teraphy until her doctors found that she has depression and anxiety.
They gave her some medication, and she started to improve quickly.
For this summer she was much better, almost like after the stroke.
However, I was exhausted mental and phisically.
Besides, my work contract had finished.
So I was in a moment of change on my live, but without any energy to face it.
So, some friends suggested my to go on a vacation for my own, in order to spend time with myself and recover energies.
I wasn't sure at first, but they were totally right.
I went for a week to a wonderful pleaces at the coast, and it was healthy for my soul.
Of course.
However, we need to be healthy in order to have a quality of live that allows us to enjoy our lives, and do exercise is a great way to do this.
So, Is it important to exercise?
Yes, but this can't keep us to do other things more important.
I've recently started to do exercise in order to be more healthy.
I already have thirty years, so I need to be more careful with me health.
The true is I feel great doing exercise, both physically and mentally.
I've lost some weight even.
However, despite the fact that I exercise, I haven't stopped to eat sweets, pies and pizzas, because I really love that kind of food.
Of course, I don't eat this everyday.
I've actually made some changes in my diet: I try to eat two pieces of fruit everyday at least.
Besides, my dinners are more light: vegetables, purees, grilled fish, salads.
And I'm trying to stop eating bread at night.
However, I don't want to obsess me with be healthy.
If one day I want to buy some pie, I'll do it.
However, I try to do this punctually, in a special day or something similar.
Well, that's a difficult question.
It obviously that the forms and ways of travel will continue to change.
We only need to think about how we travel only thirty years ago.
We have new means of transport and undoubtetly faster than the precedents.
If this continue, it's obvious that there will be many differents.
However, the differents will be determined by how the technology and the environment evolve.
If we don't discover new energy resources in order to replace coal, gas and oil, our actual means of transport wouldn't be useful anymore.
On the other hand, if the environment crisis continue, we should apply raddical actions to reduce the contamination, which could determinate how we travel.
I can't say how we'll travel in the future, but what I can say without any doubt is that we need to become more aware of the Earth's limits.
We should try harder to reduce the use of pollutigs means of transport, and start to use public transportation or bykes instead.
I personally don't have my own car, and always use buses, the underground and trains to travel.
